---
import ArticleLayout from "../../components/ArticleLayout.astro";

const title = "Atoms: The LEGO of Nature — Science";
const updated = "Updated: 2026";
---

<ArticleLayout title={title}>
  <article class="page">
    <header>
      <div class="hero-top">
        <a class="back" href="/">← Back to Atlas</a>
        <span class="chip">CHEMISTRY</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Atoms: The LEGO of Nature</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Atoms combine in structured ways to create every material, from air to steel to DNA.</p>
      <p class="subtitle">{updated}</p>
    </header>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Key ideas</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card"><h3>Structure drives behavior</h3><p>Proton count defines element identity; electron arrangement drives chemistry.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Bonds are energy decisions</h3><p>Atoms bond when shared or transferred electrons lower total energy.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Periodic trends are predictive</h3><p>The periodic table is a map of reactivity, size, and bonding style.</p></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Mental model</h2>
      <div class="card">
        <ul>
        <li>Nucleus sets element type.</li>
        <li>Electrons occupy quantized shells and orbitals.</li>
        <li>Bonding patterns scale into molecules and materials.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faq">
        <details><summary>Are atoms mostly empty space?</summary><p>Yes, most volume is electron probability cloud around a tiny dense nucleus.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Why are some elements reactive?</summary><p>Valence electrons seek lower-energy configurations via bonding.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Why does this matter in daily life?</summary><p>Cooking, batteries, medicine, and construction all depend on atomic behavior.</p></details>
      </div>
    </section>

    <nav class="footnav">
      <a class="btn" href="/science">← Science index</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/future">Explore Future →</a>
    </nav>
  </article>

</ArticleLayout>
